{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":984,"text":"The \"Dirty Jobs\" crew and I were called"},{"time":3088,"text":"to a little town\nin Colorado, called Craig."},{"time":5882,"text":"It's only a couple dozen square miles."},{"time":7723,"text":"It's in the Rockies."},{"time":8985,"text":"And the job in question was sheep rancher."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11553,"text":"My role on the show, for those of you\nwho haven't seen it -- it's pretty simple."},{"time":15360,"text":"I'm an apprentice,"},{"time":16570,"text":"and I work with the people\nwho do the jobs in question."},{"time":19318,"text":"And my responsibilities\nare to simply try and keep up,"},{"time":22318,"text":"and give an honest account\nof what it's like to be these people"},{"time":25540,"text":"for one day in their life."},{"time":27000,"text":"The job in question: herding sheep."},{"time":29598,"text":"Great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30775,"text":"We go to Craig and we check into a hotel,"},{"time":34110,"text":"and I realize the next day"},{"time":36250,"text":"that castration is going to be\nan absolute part of this work."},{"time":40364,"text":"Normally, I never do any research at all."},{"time":43000,"text":"But this is a touchy subject,\nand I work for the Discovery Channel,"},{"time":46511,"text":"and we want to portray accurately\nwhatever it is we do."},{"time":51142,"text":"And we certainly want to do it\nwith a lot of respect for the animals."},{"time":56000,"text":"So I call the Humane Society and I say,"},{"time":58088,"text":"\"Look, I'm going to be castrating\nsome lambs. Can you tell me the deal?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":61526,"text":"And they're like, \"Yeah,\nit's pretty straightforward.\""},{"time":64087,"text":"They use a band, basically, a rubber band,\nlike this, only a little smaller."},{"time":70152,"text":"This one was actually\naround the playing cards"},{"time":72373,"text":"I got yesterday --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":73580,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":75126,"text":"But it had a certain familiarity to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77041,"text":"And I said, \"Well, what exactly\nis the process?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":80247,"text":"And they said, \"The band\nis applied to the tail, tightly."},{"time":83116,"text":"And then another band is applied\nto the scrotum, tightly."},{"time":87500,"text":"Blood flow is slowly retarded;"},{"time":89000,"text":"a week later the parts\nin question fall off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91120,"text":"\"Great -- got it.\""},{"time":92296,"text":"OK, I call the SPCA to confirm this."},{"time":94903,"text":"They confirm it."},{"time":96094,"text":"I also call PETA just for fun,"},{"time":97584,"text":"and they don't like it,\nbut they confirm it."},{"time":99754,"text":"OK, that's basically how you do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101465,"text":"So the next day I go out."},{"time":102877,"text":"And I'm given a horse\nand we go get the lambs"},{"time":105246,"text":"and we take them to a pen that we built,"},{"time":107306,"text":"and we go about the business\nof animal husbandry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111000,"text":"Melanie is the wife of Albert."},{"time":112469,"text":"Albert is the shepherd in question."},{"time":114190,"text":"Melanie picks up the lamb,\none hand on both legs on the right,"},{"time":118297,"text":"likewise on the left."},{"time":119734,"text":"Lamb goes on the post, she opens it up."},{"time":121937,"text":"Alright. Great."},{"time":123135,"text":"Albert goes in, I follow Albert,\nthe crew is around."},{"time":125806,"text":"I always watch the process done\nthe first time before I try it."},{"time":129305,"text":"Being an apprentice,\nyou know, you do that."},{"time":131616,"text":"Albert reaches in his pocket to pull out,\nyou know, this black rubber band,"},{"time":135218,"text":"but what comes out instead is a knife."},{"time":138412,"text":"And I'm like, \"Hmm, that's not\nrubber at all,\" you know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":141077,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":142290,"text":"And he kind of flicked it open\nin a way that caught the sun"},{"time":145108,"text":"that was just coming\nover the Rockies, it was very --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":147670,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":149210,"text":"It was ... it was impressive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151989,"text":"In the space of about two seconds,"},{"time":153830,"text":"Albert had the knife\nbetween the cartilage of the tail,"},{"time":157635,"text":"right next to the butt of the lamb,"},{"time":160306,"text":"and very quickly, the tail was gone\nand in the bucket that I was holding."},{"time":163866,"text":"A second later, with a big thumb\nand a well-calloused forefinger,"},{"time":167459,"text":"he had the scrotum firmly in his grasp."},{"time":170386,"text":"And he pulled it toward him, like so,"},{"time":172235,"text":"and he took the knife\nand he put it on the tip."},{"time":174473,"text":"\"Now, you think you know\nwhat's coming, Michael,"},{"time":177107,"text":"You don't, OK?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":178393,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":179437,"text":"He snips it, throws the tip\nover his shoulder,"},{"time":182346,"text":"and then grabs the scrotum\nand pushes it upward,"},{"time":184686,"text":"and then his head dips down,\nobscuring my view."},{"time":188609,"text":"But what I hear is a slurping sound,"},{"time":190840,"text":"and a noise that sounds like Velcro\nbeing yanked off a sticky wall,"},{"time":194777,"text":"and I am not even kidding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197724,"text":"Can we roll the video?"},{"time":198901,"text":"No, I'm kidding, we don't --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":200267,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":202287,"text":"I thought it best to talk in pictures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205266,"text":"I do something now I've never, ever done\non a \"Dirty Jobs\" shoot, ever."},{"time":209295,"text":"I say, \"Time out. Stop.\""},{"time":211617,"text":"You guys know the show, we use take one;\nwe don't do take two."},{"time":214569,"text":"There's no writing, there's no scripting,\nthere's no nonsense."},{"time":217511,"text":"We don't fool around, we don't rehearse --"},{"time":219688,"text":"we shoot what we get!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":221110,"text":"I said, \"Stop. This is nuts.\""},{"time":223255,"text":"I mean --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":224433,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":225742,"text":"\"This is crazy."},{"time":227590,"text":"We can't do this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":229243,"text":"And Albert's like, \"What?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":230515,"text":"And I'm like, \"I don't know\nwhat just happened,"},{"time":232736,"text":"but there are testicles in this bucket,"},{"time":234692,"text":"and that's not how we do it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":236132,"text":"He said \"Well, that's how we do it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":237914,"text":"I said, \"Why would you do it this way?\""},{"time":239881,"text":"And before I even let him explain,"},{"time":241572,"text":"I said, \"I want to do it the right way,\nwith the rubber bands.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":244577,"text":"And he says, \"Like the Humane Society?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":246495,"text":"I said, \"Yes, like the Humane Society."},{"time":248357,"text":"Let's do something that doesn't make\nthe lamb squeal and bleed."},{"time":251966,"text":"We're on in five continents, dude!"},{"time":253616,"text":"We're on twice a day\non the Discovery -- we can't do this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":256424,"text":"He says, \"OK.\""},{"time":257627,"text":"He goes to his box and pulls out\na bag of these little rubber bands."},{"time":260904,"text":"Melanie picks up another lamb,\nputs it on the post,"},{"time":263436,"text":"band goes on the tail,\nband goes on the scrotum."},{"time":266178,"text":"Lamb goes on the ground,\nlamb takes two steps, falls down,"},{"time":269974,"text":"gets up, shakes a little,"},{"time":272473,"text":"takes another couple steps, falls down."},{"time":274864,"text":"I'm like, this is not a good sign\nfor this lamb, at all."},{"time":278847,"text":"Gets up, walks to the corner."},{"time":280544,"text":"It's quivering, and it lies\ndown and it's in obvious distress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284157,"text":"And I'm looking at the lamb\nand I say, \"Albert, how long?"},{"time":288000,"text":"When does he get up?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":289749,"text":"He's like, \"A day?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":291587,"text":"I said, \"A day! How long does\nit take them to fall off?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":294249,"text":"\"A week.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":295448,"text":"Meanwhile, the lamb that he had just done\nhis little procedure on"},{"time":300830,"text":"is, you know, he's just prancing\naround, bleeding stopped."},{"time":304924,"text":"He's, you know, nibbling\non some grass, frolicking."},{"time":308212,"text":"And I was just so blown away\nat how completely wrong I was,"},{"time":313226,"text":"in that second."},{"time":314865,"text":"And I was reminded how utterly wrong\nI am, so much of the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318984,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":320104,"text":"And I was especially reminded"},{"time":321920,"text":"of what a ridiculously\nshort straw I had that day,"},{"time":325216,"text":"because now I had to do\nwhat Albert had just done,"},{"time":327707,"text":"and there are like 100\nof these lambs in the pen."},{"time":331103,"text":"And suddenly, this whole thing's starting\nto feel like a German porno,"},{"time":334577,"text":"and I'm like --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335916,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":338493,"text":"Melanie picks up the lamb,\nputs it on the post, opens it up."},{"time":342074,"text":"Albert hands me the knife."},{"time":343365,"text":"I go in, tail comes off."},{"time":345088,"text":"I go in, I grab the scrotum,\ntip comes off."},{"time":348218,"text":"Albert instructs, \"Push it way up there.\""},{"time":350588,"text":"I do."},{"time":351763,"text":"\"Push it further.\""},{"time":352938,"text":"I do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354113,"text":"The testicles emerge. They look\nlike thumbs, coming right at you."},{"time":357412,"text":"And he says, \"Bite 'em."},{"time":359055,"text":"Just bite 'em off.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":361059,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":362209,"text":"And I heard him, I heard all the words --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":364322,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":368934,"text":"Like, how did I get here?"},{"time":370577,"text":"How did -- I mean --"},{"time":372483,"text":"how did I get here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":374483,"text":"It's just -- it's one of those moments\nwhere the brain goes off on its own,"},{"time":379852,"text":"and suddenly, I'm standing\nthere in the Rockies,"},{"time":383000,"text":"and all I can think of is the Aristotelian\ndefinition of a tragedy."},{"time":387410,"text":"You know, Aristotle says\na tragedy is that moment"},{"time":391535,"text":"when the hero comes face to face\nwith his true identity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395115,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":396484,"text":"And I'm like, \"What is this\njacked-up metaphor?"},{"time":398790,"text":"I don't like what I'm thinking right now.\""},{"time":400862,"text":"And I can't get this thought\nout of my head,"},{"time":402979,"text":"and I can't get that vision\nout of my sight,"},{"time":405111,"text":"so I did what I had to do."},{"time":407464,"text":"I went in and I took them."},{"time":409489,"text":"I took them like this,"},{"time":410874,"text":"and I yanked my head back."},{"time":413692,"text":"And I'm standing there\nwith two testicles on my chin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417513,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419458,"text":"And now I can't get --\nI can't shake the metaphor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422634,"text":"I'm still in \"Poetics,\" in Aristotle,\nand I'm thinking --"},{"time":426300,"text":"out of nowhere, two terms come crashing\ninto my head, that I hadn't heard"},{"time":429799,"text":"since my classics professor in college\ndrilled them there."},{"time":432939,"text":"And they are \"anagnorisis\"\nand \"peripeteia.\""},{"time":435632,"text":"Anagnorisis and peripeteia."},{"time":437983,"text":"Anagnorisis is the Greek\nword for discovery."},{"time":442320,"text":"Literally, the transition from ignorance\nto knowledge is anagnorisis."},{"time":448370,"text":"It's what our network does;\nit's what \"Dirty Jobs\" is."},{"time":451736,"text":"And I'm up to my neck\nin anagnorises every single day."},{"time":455798,"text":"Great."},{"time":456977,"text":"The other word, peripeteia,"},{"time":459139,"text":"that's the moment\nin the great tragedies --"},{"time":464477,"text":"Euripides and Sophocles."},{"time":466739,"text":"That's the moment where Oedipus has\nhis moment, where he suddenly realizes"},{"time":472268,"text":"that hot chick he's been sleeping with\nand having babies with"},{"time":475187,"text":"is his mother."},{"time":476610,"text":"That's peripety, or peripeteia."},{"time":479629,"text":"And this metaphor in my head --"},{"time":481812,"text":"I've got anagnorisis\nand peripeteia on my chin --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":484577,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486866,"text":"I've got to tell you,\nit's such a great device, though."},{"time":489494,"text":"When you start to look for peripeteia,"},{"time":492091,"text":"you find it everywhere."},{"time":493652,"text":"I mean, Bruce Willis\nin \"The Sixth Sense,\" right?"},{"time":496589,"text":"Spends the whole movie trying to help\nthe little kid who sees dead people,"},{"time":500169,"text":"and then -- boom! -- \"Oh, I'm dead.\""},{"time":501918,"text":"Peripeteia. You know?"},{"time":503102,"text":"It's crushing when the audience\nsees it the right way."},{"time":506596,"text":"Neo in \"The Matrix,\" you know?"},{"time":509121,"text":"\"Oh, I'm living in a computer program."},{"time":511120,"text":"That's weird.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":512707,"text":"These discoveries\nthat lead to sudden realizations."},{"time":516283,"text":"And I've been having them,\nover 200 dirty jobs,"},{"time":518984,"text":"I have them all the time, but that one --"},{"time":521140,"text":"that one drilled something home\nin a way that I just wasn't prepared for."},{"time":525985,"text":"And, as I stood there,"},{"time":528076,"text":"looking at the happy lamb\nthat I had just defiled --"},{"time":533707,"text":"but it looked OK;"},{"time":535520,"text":"looking at that poor other little thing\nthat I'd done it the right way on,"},{"time":539821,"text":"and I just was struck by --"},{"time":541499,"text":"if I'm wrong about that,"},{"time":545753,"text":"and if I'm wrong so often,\nin a literal way,"},{"time":548144,"text":"what other peripatetic misconceptions\nmight I be able to comment upon?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":553455,"text":"Because, look --\nI'm not a social anthropologist,"},{"time":555956,"text":"but I have a friend who is."},{"time":557296,"text":"And I talk to him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":560551,"text":"And he says, \"Hey Mike, look."},{"time":562077,"text":"I don't know if your brain is interested\nin this sort of thing or not,"},{"time":566085,"text":"but do you realize\nyou've shot in every state?"},{"time":568379,"text":"You've worked in mining,\nyou've worked in fishing,"},{"time":571675,"text":"you've worked in steel,\nyou've worked in every major industry."},{"time":575367,"text":"You've had your back\nshoulder to shoulder with these guys"},{"time":578446,"text":"that our politicians are desperate\nto relate to every four years, right?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":582076,"text":"I can still see Hillary\ndoing the shots of rye,"},{"time":584716,"text":"dribbling down her chin,\nwith the steel workers."},{"time":587040,"text":"I mean, these are the people\nthat I work with every single day."},{"time":590639,"text":"\"And if you have something to say\nabout their thoughts, collectively,"},{"time":594671,"text":"it might be time to think about it."},{"time":596609,"text":"Because, dude, you know, four years.\""},{"time":600200,"text":"So, that's in my head,\ntesticles are on my chin,"},{"time":604451,"text":"thoughts are bouncing around."},{"time":606360,"text":"And, after that shoot,\n\"Dirty Jobs\" really didn't change,"},{"time":611753,"text":"in terms of what the show is,\nbut it changed for me, personally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615231,"text":"And now, when I talk about the show,"},{"time":617134,"text":"I no longer just tell the story\nyou heard and 190 like it."},{"time":623506,"text":"I do, but I also start to talk\nabout some of the other things"},{"time":626739,"text":"I got wrong;"},{"time":627938,"text":"some of the other notions of work"},{"time":629988,"text":"that I've just been assuming\nare sacrosanct,"},{"time":633894,"text":"and they're not."},{"time":635069,"text":"People with dirty jobs\nare happier than you think."},{"time":638000,"text":"As a group, they're\nthe happiest people I know."},{"time":641035,"text":"And I don't want to start whistling\n\"Look for the Union Label,\""},{"time":644041,"text":"and all that happy-worker crap."},{"time":645549,"text":"I'm just telling you\nthat these are balanced people"},{"time":647970,"text":"who do unthinkable work."},{"time":649149,"text":"Roadkill picker-uppers whistle\nwhile they work, I swear to God --"},{"time":652274,"text":"I did it with them."},{"time":653452,"text":"They've got this amazing\nsort of symmetry to their life."},{"time":657681,"text":"And I see it over and over and over again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660334,"text":"So I started to wonder what would happen"},{"time":662448,"text":"if we challenged\nsome of these sacred cows?"},{"time":665515,"text":"Follow your passion --"},{"time":667227,"text":"we've been talking about it\nhere for the last 36 hours."},{"time":670875,"text":"Follow your passion -- what could\npossibly be wrong with that?"},{"time":673841,"text":"It's probably the worst advice I ever got."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675868,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":676966,"text":"Follow your dreams and go broke, right?"},{"time":678868,"text":"I mean, that's all I heard growing up."},{"time":680714,"text":"I didn't know what to do with my life,"},{"time":682564,"text":"but I was told if you follow your passion,\nit's going to work out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685729,"text":"I can give you 30 examples right now."},{"time":687554,"text":"Bob Combs, the pig farmer in Las Vegas"},{"time":689651,"text":"who collects the uneaten scraps\nof food from the casinos"},{"time":692333,"text":"and feeds them to his swine."},{"time":694044,"text":"Why?"},{"time":695219,"text":"Because there's so much protein\nin the stuff we don't eat,"},{"time":698017,"text":"his pigs grow at twice the normal speed,\nand he's one rich pig farmer."},{"time":701358,"text":"He's good for the environment,"},{"time":702819,"text":"he spends his days\ndoing this incredible service,"},{"time":705147,"text":"and he smells like hell,\nbut God bless him."},{"time":707179,"text":"He's making a great living."},{"time":708501,"text":"You ask him, \"Did you follow\nyour passion here?\""},{"time":710794,"text":"and he'd laugh at you."},{"time":711973,"text":"The guy's worth -- he just got offered\nlike 60 million dollars for his farm"},{"time":716242,"text":"and turned it down, outside of Vegas."},{"time":718472,"text":"He didn't follow his passion."},{"time":719917,"text":"He stepped back and he watched\nwhere everybody was going,"},{"time":722887,"text":"and he went the other way."},{"time":725200,"text":"And I hear that story over and over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727140,"text":"Matt Freund, a dairy farmer\nin New Canaan, Connecticut,"},{"time":730736,"text":"who woke up one day and realized"},{"time":732486,"text":"the crap from his cows\nwas worth more than their milk,"},{"time":735223,"text":"if he could use it to make\nthese biodegradable flowerpots."},{"time":739129,"text":"Now he's selling them to Walmart, right?"},{"time":742429,"text":"Follow his passion? The guy's -- come on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745486,"text":"So I started to look at passion,"},{"time":747717,"text":"I started to look\nat efficiency vs. effectiveness."},{"time":751839,"text":"As Tim talked about earlier,\nthat's a huge distinction."},{"time":755032,"text":"I started to look at teamwork\nand determination."},{"time":757535,"text":"And basically, all those platitudes\nthey call \"successories\""},{"time":760555,"text":"that hang with that schmaltzy art\nin boardrooms around the world right now,"},{"time":764506,"text":"that stuff -- it's suddenly\nall been turned on its head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769418,"text":"Safety. Safety first is ..."},{"time":773079,"text":"Going back to OSHA and PETA\nand the Humane Society:"},{"time":777025,"text":"What if OSHA got it wrong?"},{"time":779325,"text":"I mean -- this is heresy,\nwhat I'm about to say --"},{"time":781696,"text":"but what if it's really safety third?"},{"time":784523,"text":"Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":785717,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":787167,"text":"No, I mean, really."},{"time":789404,"text":"What I mean to say is:"},{"time":791236,"text":"I value my safety on these crazy jobs"},{"time":793724,"text":"as much as the people\nthat I'm working with,"},{"time":796310,"text":"but the ones who really get it done --"},{"time":798610,"text":"they're not out there\ntalking about safety first."},{"time":801954,"text":"They know that other things come first --"},{"time":804000,"text":"the business of doing\nthe work comes first,"},{"time":806072,"text":"the business of getting it done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807919,"text":"And I'll never forget,\nup in the Bering Sea,"},{"time":810704,"text":"I was on a crab boat\nwith the \"Deadliest Catch\" guys --"},{"time":813462,"text":"which I also work on in the first season."},{"time":815778,"text":"We were about 100 miles\noff the coast of Russia:"},{"time":818478,"text":"50-foot seas, big waves, green water\ncoming over the wheelhouse, right?"},{"time":822899,"text":"Most hazardous environment I'd ever seen,"},{"time":825000,"text":"and I was back with a guy,\nlashing the pots down."},{"time":827922,"text":"So I'm 40 feet off the deck,"},{"time":830102,"text":"which is like looking down\nat the top of your shoe, you know,"},{"time":833024,"text":"and it's doing this in the ocean."},{"time":834655,"text":"Unspeakably dangerous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":835835,"text":"I scamper down, I go into the wheelhouse"},{"time":837793,"text":"and I say, with some level of incredulity,"},{"time":841138,"text":"\"Captain -- OSHA?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":842975,"text":"And he says, \"OSHA? Ocean.\""},{"time":845556,"text":"And he points out there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":850355,"text":"But in that moment, what he said next\ncan't be repeated in the Lower 48."},{"time":855330,"text":"It can't be repeated on any factory floor\nor any construction site."},{"time":858955,"text":"But he looked at me and said, \"Son,\" --"},{"time":860864,"text":"he's my age, by the way,\nhe calls me \"son,\" I love that --"},{"time":863635,"text":"he says, \"Son, I'm the captain\nof a crab boat."},{"time":865834,"text":"My responsibility\nis not to get you home alive."},{"time":868427,"text":"My responsibility\nis to get you home rich.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":870797,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":872285,"text":"You want to get home alive,\nthat's on you.\""},{"time":874515,"text":"And for the rest\nof that day -- safety first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877167,"text":"I mean, I was like --"},{"time":878834,"text":"So, the idea that we create\nthis sense of complacency"},{"time":885168,"text":"when all we do is talk\nabout somebody else's responsibility"},{"time":889691,"text":"as though it's our own, and vice versa."},{"time":891648,"text":"Anyhow, a whole lot of things."},{"time":893294,"text":"I could talk at length\nabout the many little distinctions we made"},{"time":896745,"text":"and the endless list of ways\nthat I got it wrong."},{"time":899625,"text":"But what it all comes down to is this:"},{"time":901984,"text":"I've formed a theory,"},{"time":903203,"text":"and I'm going to share it now\nin my remaining 2 minutes and 30 seconds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906642,"text":"It goes like this:"},{"time":908853,"text":"we've declared war on work,\nas a society -- all of us."},{"time":913841,"text":"It's a civil war."},{"time":915773,"text":"It's a cold war, really."},{"time":917690,"text":"We didn't set out to do it"},{"time":920000,"text":"and we didn't twist our mustache\nin some Machiavellian way,"},{"time":923645,"text":"but we've done it."},{"time":924891,"text":"And we've waged this war\non at least four fronts,"},{"time":928614,"text":"certainly in Hollywood."},{"time":930121,"text":"The way we portray working people on TV --"},{"time":932755,"text":"it's laughable."},{"time":934000,"text":"If there's a plumber, he's 300 pounds"},{"time":935798,"text":"and he's got a giant butt crack, admit it."},{"time":937913,"text":"You see him all the time."},{"time":939188,"text":"That's what plumbers look like, right?"},{"time":941693,"text":"We turn them into heroes,\nor we turn them into punch lines."},{"time":944905,"text":"That's what TV does."},{"time":946111,"text":"We try hard on \"Dirty Jobs\"\nnot to do that,"},{"time":948476,"text":"which is why I do the work\nand I don't cheat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952222,"text":"But, we've waged this war\non Madison Avenue."},{"time":955111,"text":"So many of the commercials that come out\nthere in the way of a message --"},{"time":959524,"text":"what's really being said?"},{"time":961001,"text":"\"Your life would be better\nif you could work a little less,"},{"time":963807,"text":"didn't have to work so hard,\ngot home a little earlier,"},{"time":966664,"text":"could retire a little faster,\npunch out a little sooner.\""},{"time":969377,"text":"It's all in there,\nover and over, again and again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972025,"text":"Washington?"},{"time":973200,"text":"I can't even begin to talk\nabout the deals and policies in place"},{"time":976255,"text":"that affect the bottom-line reality\nof the available jobs,"},{"time":979788,"text":"because I don't really know; I just know\nthat that's a front in this war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":983375,"text":"And right here, guys -- Silicon Valley."},{"time":985494,"text":"I mean -- how many people have\nan iPhone on them right now?"},{"time":988584,"text":"How many people have their BlackBerry?"},{"time":990451,"text":"We're plugged in; we're connected."},{"time":992265,"text":"I would never suggest for a second"},{"time":994552,"text":"that something bad\nhas come out of the tech revolution."},{"time":997547,"text":"Good grief, not to this crowd."}]},{"cues":[{"time":999166,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1001321,"text":"But I would suggest"},{"time":1002628,"text":"that innovation without imitation\nis a complete waste of time."},{"time":1007972,"text":"And nobody celebrates imitation"},{"time":1010469,"text":"the way \"Dirty Jobs\" guys\nknow it has to be done."},{"time":1014235,"text":"Your iPhone without those people\nmaking the same interface,"},{"time":1017671,"text":"the same circuitry,\nthe same board, over and over --"},{"time":1020155,"text":"all of that -- that's what makes\nit equally as possible"},{"time":1023687,"text":"as the genius that goes inside of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026897,"text":"So, we've got this new toolbox. You know?"},{"time":1029754,"text":"Our tools today don't look\nlike shovels and picks."},{"time":1033364,"text":"They look like the stuff\nwe walk around with."},{"time":1036471,"text":"And so the collective\neffect of all of that"},{"time":1041714,"text":"has been this marginalization\nof lots and lots of jobs."},{"time":1047147,"text":"And I realized, probably\ntoo late in this game --"},{"time":1050174,"text":"I hope not, because I don't know\nif I can do 200 more of these things --"},{"time":1053652,"text":"but we're going to do as many as we can."},{"time":1055591,"text":"And to me, the most\nimportant thing to know"},{"time":1057676,"text":"and to really come face to face with,"},{"time":1059532,"text":"is that fact that I got it wrong\nabout a lot of things,"},{"time":1062329,"text":"not just the testicles on my chin."},{"time":1064413,"text":"I got a lot wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1067753,"text":"So, we're thinking --\nby \"we,\" I mean me --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1071776,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1073690,"text":"that the thing to do is to talk\nabout a PR campaign for work --"},{"time":1078853,"text":"manual labor, skilled labor."},{"time":1081154,"text":"Somebody needs to be out there,\ntalking about the forgotten benefits."},{"time":1086467,"text":"I'm talking about grandfather stuff,"},{"time":1088252,"text":"the stuff a lot us probably grew up with"},{"time":1090223,"text":"but we've kind of --\nyou know, kind of lost a little."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1095369,"text":"Barack wants to create\ntwo and a half million jobs."},{"time":1098382,"text":"The infrastructure is a huge deal."},{"time":1100062,"text":"This war on work that I suppose exists,\nhas casualties like any other war."},{"time":1104142,"text":"The infrastructure is the first one,"},{"time":1106000,"text":"declining trade school enrollments\nare the second one."},{"time":1108987,"text":"Every single year, fewer electricians,\nfewer carpenters, fewer plumbers,"},{"time":1113852,"text":"fewer welders, fewer pipe fitters,\nfewer steam fitters."},{"time":1118709,"text":"The infrastructure jobs that everybody\nis talking about creating"},{"time":1122404,"text":"are those guys -- the ones\nthat have been in decline, over and over."},{"time":1126104,"text":"Meanwhile, we've got\ntwo trillion dollars, at a minimum,"},{"time":1129134,"text":"according to the American Society\nof Civil Engineers,"},{"time":1131707,"text":"that we need to expend\nto even make a dent in the infrastructure,"},{"time":1134866,"text":"which is currently rated at a D minus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1137136,"text":"So, if I were running\nfor anything -- and I'm not --"},{"time":1141685,"text":"I would simply say\nthat the jobs we hope to make"},{"time":1144318,"text":"and the jobs we hope to create"},{"time":1146396,"text":"aren't going to stick unless\nthey're jobs that people want."},{"time":1149931,"text":"And I know the point of this conference"},{"time":1152550,"text":"is to celebrate things\nthat are near and dear to us,"},{"time":1155481,"text":"but I also know that clean\nand dirty aren't opposites."},{"time":1158509,"text":"They're two sides of the same coin,\njust like innovation and imitation,"},{"time":1162154,"text":"like risk and responsibility,\nlike peripeteia and anagnorisis,"},{"time":1167263,"text":"like that poor little lamb,\nwho I hope isn't quivering anymore,"},{"time":1170918,"text":"and like my time that's gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1172434,"text":"It's been great talking to you."},{"time":1174464,"text":"And get back to work, will you?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1176000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}